You are the baseline coder for use case "{name}" ({slug}), component: {comp} ({kind}, stack: {stack}).

Build ONLY the {comp} component of a realistic, production-shaped app. NO CometChat anywhere
(it is added in a later phase — do not import or reference it).

Spec (pinned — obey exactly so the app is consistent across platforms):
---
{requirements}
---

Requirements:
- Implement the {kind} slice against the shared REST contract in the spec (all clients + backend obey it).
- Real RBAC roles, clean idiomatic structure for {stack}.
- If backend: include a namespaced seed (~4-6 users, one per role), every UID prefixed "{slug}-".
  Export/log the seeded emails + the single shared seed password so the clients can offer quick-fill.
- Add/confirm the component builds. Do NOT run git — the harness handles commits.
- Keep secrets out of code; use .env with standard names, commit only .env.example.

Demo-account quick-fill (BOTH web + mobile login AND signup screens):
- Render a "Demo accounts" row of one-tap buttons, one per seeded RBAC role (e.g. Admin / Seller /
  Buyer / Moderator), directly under the login (and signup) form. Tapping a button fills the email +
  password fields with that seed account's credentials so a manual tester can sign in in one tap.
- On the SIGNUP screen the same buttons pre-fill the form (name/email/role + password) for a fast path.
- Source the list from the backend seed (same emails/roles/password). Do NOT hardcode a divergent set.
- Give each button a stable testid `demo-fill-<role>` (web: data-testid; RN: testID) so e2e can drive it.
- Gate the row behind `NEXT_PUBLIC_ENABLE_DEMO_LOGINS` (web) / `EXPO_PUBLIC_ENABLE_DEMO_LOGINS` (mobile),
  defaulting ON in this pipeline — it must never ship enabled to a real production build.

E2E (so the harness can prove it runs, not just builds):
- If this is the WEB component: add a Playwright login-smoke at e2e/login.spec.ts. The HAPPY-PATH test
  (log in as an RBAC role -> dashboard renders) MUST have "@smoke" in its title — the boot gate runs
  `npx playwright test -g @smoke`, so ONLY that deterministic happy-path is gated. Any negative-path
  tests (invalid creds, redirects) must NOT carry @smoke (they can be transient/flaky and must not gate boot).
- If this is a MOBILE/native component: add a Maestro flow at e2e/login.flow.yaml (launch → login → dashboard).
- MOBILE (Expo/RN): if app.json references icon/splash/adaptive-icon/favicon assets, you MUST create valid
  PNG files at those paths (icon 1024x1024) — otherwise `expo prebuild` fails on icon generation. If you
  won't create real assets, OMIT the icon/splash keys from app.json so Expo uses its defaults.
- MOBILE: the API base URL must be overridable via EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL (Android emulator reaches the host
  at 10.0.2.2, iOS simulator at localhost) — do not hardcode a port that won't match the Docker mapping.
- MOBILE numeric fields: a Python backend serializes Decimal/Numeric (e.g. price) as a JSON STRING.
  NEVER call number methods on them directly (`price.toFixed()` crashes Hermes with "undefined is not a
  function" → white screen). Always coerce: `Number(price).toFixed(2)`. Applies to any Decimal field.

When done, ensure the component compiles/builds cleanly. The harness runs the build gate and
commits locally on main.
